## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2b610-150"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> está pensado para ser crea una instancia una vez y volver a utilizar durante toda la vida de una aplicación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b610-150"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> is intended to be instantiated once and re-used throughout the life of an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b610-151">Crear instancias de una clase HttpClient para cada solicitud, se agotará al número de sockets disponibles con cargas elevadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b610-151">Instantiating an HttpClient class for every request will exhaust the number of sockets available under heavy loads.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b610-152">Esto provocará errores SocketException.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b610-152">This will result in SocketException errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b610-153">A continuación se muestra un ejemplo de cómo utilizar HttpClient correctamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b610-153">Below is an example using HttpClient correctly.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class GoodController : ApiController  
{  
    // OK  
    private static readonly HttpClient HttpClient;  
  
    static GoodController()  
    {  
        HttpClient = new HttpClient();  
    }  
}  
  
```
